cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.LG. 

The paper presents a model-based planner for controlling stochastic systems, such as unmanned aerial and space vehicles, in a goal-directed manner within user-specified risk bounds. This involves developing new plan representations and capabilities for risk-sensitive and goal-directed planning in a continuous domain with temporal constraints. These topics are closely related to robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), programming languages (cs.PL), and machine learning (cs.LG).
